oc:kn_2f7e0baa a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when checking thermal limits or reporting branch loading" ;
    oc:directiveContent "RATE_A = 0 means no MVA limit; enforce |S_ij| ≤ RATE_A and |S_ji| ≤ RATE_A in both directions. Branch loading % = 100 * max(|S_ij|, |S_ji|) / RATE_A when RATE_A > 0" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The limiting flow direction may differ from the dominant power transfer direction, so both must be checked independently" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_372c56be a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when computing AC branch pi-model power flow equations" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """P_ij = g * |V_i|² * inv_t2 - |V_i||V_j| * inv_t * (g*cos(δ_ij) + b*sin(δ_ij))
Q_ij = -(b + b_c/2) * |V_i|² * inv_t2 - |V_i||V_j| * inv_t * (g*sin(δ_ij) - b*cos(δ_ij))
P_ji = g * |V_j|² - |V_i||V_j| * inv_t * (g*cos(δ_ji) + b*sin(δ_ji))
Q_ji = -(b + b_c/2) * |V_j|² - |V_i||V_j| * inv_t * (g*sin(δ_ji) - b*cos(δ_ji))
|S_ij| = sqrt(P_ij² + Q_ij²)
|S_ji| = sqrt(P_ji² + Q_ji²)""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the exact equations from the task formulation that must be matched precisely" .

oc:kn_507a2783 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when computing per-unit branch flows for any network" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Parse branch data using MATPOWER field order 2. Compute series admittance g,b from BR_R,BR_X (guard r=x=0) 3. Handle transformer: tap and shift (deg→rad) 4. Compute δ_ij and δ_ji angle differences 5. Evaluate P_ij, Q_ij, P_ji, Q_ji using exact pi-model equations 6. Compute |S| in both directions 7. Convert to MVA using baseMVA" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ordered procedure ensures no step is missed and transformer/admittance special cases are handled before flow evaluation" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_6792cc7f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when aggregating branch flows into bus injections for nodal balance" ;
    oc:directiveContent """P_out[i] = Σ P_ij for all branches from bus i
Q_out[i] = Σ Q_ij for all branches from bus i
Nodal balance: P^g − P^d − G^s|V|² = P_out, Q^g − Q^d + B^s|V|² = Q_out""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This format connects branch-level flow results to the bus-level nodal balance equations used in ACOPF" ;
    oc:templateVariables "B^s",
        "G^s",
        "P^d",
        "P^g",
        "P_out",
        "Q^d",
        "Q^g",
        "Q_out" .

oc:kn_79a630e3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when handling transformer tap and phase shift in branch data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If abs(TAP) < 1e-12, treat tap = 1.0 (no transformer). Convert SHIFT from degrees to radians. Modify angle difference: δ_ij = θ_i − θ_j − shift, δ_ji = θ_j − θ_i + shift" ;
    oc:hasRationale "MATPOWER encodes zero-tap as absent transformer; proper angle shift handling is essential for phase-shifting transformers and off-nominal tap ratios" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_84e46d81 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "always when computing branch flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Work in per-unit internally; convert to MVA only at output using baseMVA: |S|_MVA = |S|_pu * baseMVA" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Per-unit normalization removes baseMVA scaling from all equations, preventing numerical errors and ensuring consistency with MATPOWER conventions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ccadeed1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "always when computing branch flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Compute flows in BOTH directions explicitly (P_ij, Q_ij, P_ji, Q_ji). Treat results as power LEAVING the from-bus and power LEAVING the to-bus respectively" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Branch losses mean S_ij ≠ −S_ji; both directions must be computed independently for correct nodal balance and limit checking" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_cdc7773d a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when debugging unexpected branch flow values" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sanity check: with SHIFT=0, TAP=1, if V_i = V_j and θ_i = θ_j, then P_ij ≈ 0 and P_ji ≈ 0 (lossless only if r=0)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This zero-state check quickly reveals sign errors, incorrect admittance computation, or unit mismatches without needing a full power flow solution" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_cf44a265 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when computing series admittance from BR_R and BR_X" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never divide by r+jx when both r=0 and x=0; instead set g=0, b=0 to avoid divide-by-zero. A pure transformer (r=x=0) should not produce meaningful series flows" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Zero impedance would produce infinite admittance, corrupting all downstream power flow calculations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f69f81af a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "when constructing the pi-model shunt elements" ;
    oc:directiveContent "BR_B is the TOTAL line charging susceptance b_c (per unit). Each end of the pi-model gets b_c/2" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The pi-model splits total charging equally to both ends; using full b_c on one side would double the shunt admittance" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

_:ref_00782f3496d20f25 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "For each branch, compute series admittance g, b from BR_R, BR_X (guard against r=x=0), extract b_c=BR_B, tap, shift" ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Per-branch admittance and transformer parameters" ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_eb3960a90b84e7d6 ;
    oc:stepId "compute-admittance" .

_:ref_112235146ed6b84c a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "For each branch, compute P_ij, Q_ij, P_ji, Q_ji using the exact pi-model equations with transformer handling" ;
